description: On high alert, France is mourning the 130 people murdered in co-ordinated attacks five years ago.
title: Paris attacks: France remembers night of terror amid jihadist threat
title_page: Paris attacks: France remembers night of terror amid jihadist threat - BBC News
maintext: Eagles of Death Metal lead singer Jesse Hughes has spoken of how he almost "became French" on the night of the Bataclan attack. "I can almost feel the physical presence of those people I love so much - those who died, who were wounded, who survived, who helped and all their families," he told Le Parisien.
